      @PutMapping("/update-seat-status") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Seat> updateSeatStatus​(@RequestParam int seatId, @RequestParam java.lang.String status) throws java.lang.Throwable
      UPDATE SEAT STATUS This method looks for the seat_id stored on the database and stores it on the seat model defined before. Then it gets the status of the current selected seat and updates it depending on what the user selected using the CRUD repository on the SeatRepository object

      status - : the status in which you want the seat to become.

    • updateSeat

      @PutMapping(value="/updateSeat", produces="application/json") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Seat> updateSeat​(@RequestBody Seat seat1) throws java.lang.Throwable
      UPDATE SEAT (ADMIN) This method takes a whole seat object in with updated values, it then finds the seat in the database that has a corresponding id to the one it has receieved in parameter. it then sets the current seat to the newly added seat attributes from the parameter object. Once the updated values are added, the seat gets updated in the database using the CRUD operations from the repository.
      Parameters:
      Seat - seat : the object with updated seat values
      Throws:
      java.lang.Throwable
